<paragraph id="8BA236E0FF87FFC3FF56FA4FFA2FF82E" blockId="8.[151,1437,1482,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">
<materialsCitation id="3B753CBDFF87FFC3FF56FA4FFA2FF82E" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1291011496" collectionCode="AMNH, ICZN" collectorName="J. A. Allen &amp; Dr. G." country="Iceland" county="The" location="Allen" municipality="Allen" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" specimenCount="8" stateProvince="Massachusetts" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis id="B969EAF2FF87FFC3FF56FA4FFEFDFA16" bold="true" box="[151,330,1482,1507]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF87FFC3FF56FA4FFF65FA16" box="[151,210,1482,1507]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">Type</typeStatus>
material.
</emphasis>
<collectingCounty id="62C34E6CFF87FFC3FE97FA4FFE35FA16" box="[342,386,1482,1507]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">The</collectingCounty>
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF87FFC3FE4FFA4EFE09FA16" box="[398,446,1483,1507]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1D4D63FF87FFC3FE2FFA4EFD1FFA16" box="[494,680,1483,1507]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bauri">
<emphasis id="B969EAF2FF87FFC3FE2FFA4EFD1FFA16" box="[494,680,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">Oryzomys bauri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described by 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BC6AC9AFF87FFC3FC9AFA4FFC2EFA16" box="[859,921,1482,1507]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">Allen</collectingMunicipality>
in 1892, is an adult male, part of a series composed by additional four specimens in alcohol: “I male two-thirds grown, I male half grown, I female adult and I female about half grown”, all captured in Barrington 
<collectingCountry id="F30A7670FF87FFC3FCC9F997FCE7F9DE" box="[776,848,1554,1579]" name="Iceland" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">Island</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8C4B11FF87FFC3FC9DF997FC5AF9DE" author="Allen" box="[860,1005,1554,1579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" refString="Allen, J. A. (1892) On a small collection of mammals from the Galapagos Islands, collected by Dr. G. Baur. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 4, 47 - 50." type="journal article" year="1892">
<location id="8EC2603BFF87FFC3FC9DF997FC2DF9DE" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF87FFC3FC9DF997FC2DF9DE" box="[860,922,1554,1579]" country="Iceland" county="The" municipality="Allen" name="Allen" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" stateProvince="Massachusetts">Allen</location>
(1892)
</bibRefCitation>
also mentioned the existence of three skins preserved in antiseptic solution. 
<location id="8EC2603BFF87FFC3FD83F9B3FD32F9BA" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF87FFC3FD83F9B3FD32F9BA" box="[578,645,1590,1615]" country="Iceland" county="The" municipality="Allen" name="These" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" stateProvince="Massachusetts">These</location>
specimens were sent to 
<collectorName id="26E85336FF87FFC3FC54F9B2FBB9F9BA" box="[917,1038,1590,1615]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">J. A. Allen</collectorName>
by 
<collectorName id="26E85336FF87FFC3FBF9F9B2FBCDF9BA" box="[1080,1146,1591,1615]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">Dr. G.</collectorName>
Baur of 
<location id="8EC2603BFF87FFC3FB1DF9B3FA2FF9BA" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF87FFC3FB1DF9B3FA2FF9BA" box="[1244,1432,1590,1615]" country="Iceland" county="The" municipality="Allen" name="Clark University" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" stateProvince="Massachusetts">Clark University</location>
, 
<location id="8EC2603BFF87FFC3FF56F9DEFEBDF987" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF87FFC3FF56F9DEFEBDF987" box="[151,266,1627,1650]" country="Iceland" county="The" municipality="Allen" name="Worcester" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" stateProvince="Massachusetts">Worcester</location>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D9F802FF87FFC3FED5F9DFFE0EF986" box="[276,441,1626,1651]" country="United States of America" name="Massachusetts" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">Massachusetts</collectingRegion>
, and were obtained during the 
<location id="8EC2603BFF87FFC3FCCEF9DFFC4CF986" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF87FFC3FCCEF9DFFC4CF986" box="[783,1019,1626,1651]" country="Iceland" county="The" municipality="Allen" name="Salisbury Expedition" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" stateProvince="Massachusetts">Salisbury Expedition</location>
in the 
<collectingRegion id="49D9F802FF87FFC3FB86F9DFFB0AF986" box="[1095,1213,1626,1651]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">Galapagos</collectingRegion>
Archipelago (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8C4B11FF87FFC3FA9DF9DFFF64F962" author="Allen" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" refString="Allen, J. A. (1892) On a small collection of mammals from the Galapagos Islands, collected by Dr. G. Baur. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 4, 47 - 50." type="journal article" year="1892">Allen 1892</bibRefCitation>
). 
<location id="8EC2603BFF87FFC3FF26F9FBFE9CF962" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF87FFC3FF26F9FBFE9CF962" box="[231,299,1662,1687]" country="Iceland" county="The" municipality="Allen" name="Those" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" stateProvince="Massachusetts">Those</location>
specimens were probably loaned to the 
<collectionCode id="ED0CAE25FF87FFC3FD35F9FAFCFEF962" box="[756,841,1663,1687]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">AMNH</collectionCode>
through 
<collectorName id="26E85336FF87FFC3FC71F9FAFB99F962" box="[944,1070,1662,1687]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">J. A. Allen</collectorName>
, however they are not housed at the 
<collectionCode id="ED0CAE25FF87FFC3FF01F926FEAFF94E" box="[192,280,1699,1723]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">AMNH</collectionCode>
, neither in the regular nor in the 
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF87FFC3FD45F926FD03F94E" box="[644,692,1699,1723]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">type</typeStatus>
collections. As a matter of fact, on the original description there is no information on where this material may have been deposited, or any mention to voucher field numbers or collection numbers. We contacted Clark University (Jamie Fitzgerald and Paula Kupstas 
<emphasis id="B969EAF2FF87FFC3FB06F96EFAA6F8F6" box="[1223,1297,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">in litt.</emphasis>
), and were informed that most rodents deposited there lack labels and that most of their identifying information has been lost over the last decades. Therefore, we believe that the designation of a 
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF87FFC3FC74F8B6FBB9F8BE" box="[949,1038,1843,1867]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">neotype</typeStatus>
is important to define the nominal taxon objectively. We support this claim, since we consider that the 
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF87FFC3FC4FF8D2FC09F89A" box="[910,958,1879,1903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">type</typeStatus>
is lost, and we believe that this attends the qualifying conditions established by the 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8C4B11FF87FFC3FDBAF8FEFCA3F866" author="ICZN" box="[635,788,1915,1939]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" refString="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature [ICZN] (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 335 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode id="ED0CAE25FF87FFC3FDBAF8FEFD0BF866" box="[635,700,1915,1939]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">ICZN</collectionCode>
(1999)
</bibRefCitation>
article 75.3.4. Moreover, we selected as a 
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF87FFC3FAE2F8FEFAC8F866" box="[1315,1407,1915,1939]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">neotype</typeStatus>
, a specimen from the same 
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF87FFC3FE01F81AFE47F842" box="[448,496,1951,1975]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">type</typeStatus>
locality (article 75.3.6), that is housed at the Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, a traditional institution that houses several 
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF87FFC3FD46F846FD00F82E" box="[647,695,1987,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">type</typeStatus>
specimens (article 75.3.7), attending 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8C4B11FF87FFC3FBA5F846FB40F82E" author="ICZN" box="[1124,1271,1987,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485" refString="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature [ICZN] (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 335 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode id="ED0CAE25FF87FFC3FBA5F846FB12F82E" box="[1124,1189,1987,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="485">ICZN</collectionCode>
(1999)
</bibRefCitation>
requirements.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF626668FF86FFC2FF56F823FD58F82F" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261823/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="486" targetBox="[253,1332,193,1930]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BA236E0FF86FFC2FF56F823FD58F82F" blockId="9.[151,1436,1958,2010]" pageId="9" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis id="B969EAF2FF86FFC2FF56F823FEA2F84E" bold="true" box="[151,277,1958,1980]" pageId="9" pageNumber="486">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
Dorsal, ventral and lateral views of the skull, and lateral view of the mandible of the specimen MVZ 145379, neotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1D4D63FF86FFC2FEC8F840FD9EF82F" authority="Allen, 1892" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1892" box="[265,553,1988,2010]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="9" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bauri">
<emphasis id="B969EAF2FF86FFC2FEC8F840FE1CF82F" box="[265,427,1988,2010]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="486">Oryzomys bauri</emphasis>
Allen, 1892
</taxonomicName>
(ONL: 34.53 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA236E0FF85FFC1FF56FF1DFA31FE90" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">
NEOTYPE: Adult female, deposited at the Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, under number MVZ 145379, collected by J. L. Patton, in 
<date id="FFA31020FF85FFC1FEA0FF39FE78FF21" box="[353,463,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487" value="1974-01-21">21.I.1974</date>
, number JLP 3951. It is preserved in skin, skull and tissue in ethanol; skin and skull are in good condition (
<figureCitation id="13262A65FF85FFC1FEBCFF5AFE70FF0D" box="[381,455,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1958,1980]" captionTargetBox="[253,1332,193,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[253,1333,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal, ventral and lateral views of the skull, and lateral view of the mandible of the specimen MVZ 145379, neotype of Oryzomys bauri Allen, 1892 (ONL: 34.53 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261823/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Other ten specimens are also part of the series, all deposited in the Museum of Vertebrate Zoology: five females, MVZ145372, MVZ145373, MVZ145376, MVZ145377, MVZ145379, and five males, MVZ145374, MVZ145375, MVZ145378, MVZ145380, MVZ145381. We chose this specimen since it is well preserved and harbors important information associated, such as skin, skull and tissue preserved on alcohol.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236E0FF85FFC1FF06FEEAFF7DFE59" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis id="B969EAF2FF85FFC1FF06FEEAFECCFE7D" bold="true" box="[199,379,367,392]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">Type condition</emphasis>
. Specimen preserved in skin and skull; both are in excellent condition, without any broken part.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236E0FF85FFC1FF06FE32FDCEFD95" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">
<materialsCitation id="3B753CBDFF85FFC1FF06FE32FC95FDED" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1291011491" country="Ecuador" county="Barrington Island" location="Barrington Cove" municipality="Barrington Cove" pageId="10" pageNumber="487" specimenCount="2" stateProvince="Galapagos" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis id="B969EAF2FF85FFC1FF06FE32FED3FE25" bold="true" box="[199,356,439,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF85FFC1FF06FE32FEB5FE25" box="[199,258,439,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">Type</typeStatus>
locality
</emphasis>
. According to the original label, the 
<typeStatus id="54A68842FF85FFC1FCECFE3DFC31FE25" box="[813,902,440,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">neotype</typeStatus>
is (as the original missing specimens) from “ 
<location id="8EC2603BFF85FFC1FF60FE59FED3FE01" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF85FFC1FF60FE59FED3FE01" box="[161,356,476,501]" country="Ecuador" county="Barrington Island" municipality="Barrington Cove" name="Barrington Cove" pageId="10" pageNumber="487" stateProvince="Galapagos">Barrington Cove</location>
, 
<location id="8EC2603BFF85FFC1FEB0FE59FD95FE00" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF85FFC1FEB0FE59FD95FE00" box="[369,546,476,501]" country="Ecuador" county="Barrington Island" municipality="Barrington Cove" name="Isla Barrington" pageId="10" pageNumber="487" stateProvince="Galapagos">Isla Barrington</location>
”. 
<location id="8EC2603BFF85FFC1FDF9FE58FDC6FE01" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B487F6FF87FFC0FF56FA06FD6DFD38:8EC2603BFF85FFC1FDF9FE58FDC6FE01" box="[568,625,477,500]" country="Ecuador" county="Barrington Island" municipality="Barrington Cove" name="Here" pageId="10" pageNumber="487" stateProvince="Galapagos">Here</location>
, we propose the following arrangement: “ 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BC6AC9AFF85FFC1FB92FE59FAA2FE01" box="[1107,1301,476,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">Barrington Cove</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<collectingCounty id="62C34E6CFF85FFC1FAE2FE59FF6CFDED" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">Barrington Island</collectingCounty>
[= Isla Santa Fe], 
<collectingRegion id="49D9F802FF85FFC1FE6AFE7AFD96FDED" box="[427,545,511,536]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="10" pageNumber="487">Galapagos</collectingRegion>
Archipelago, 
